title: What are some good cover songs to listen to? - Quora

response.answer_text: Moonlight Shadow - Annie Haslem  Moonlight Shadow - Blackmore’s Night (Orig. Mike Oldfield)  The original is also excellent Ocean Gypsy - Blackmore’s Night (orig. Renaissance)  Again the original is also excellent A Few More by Blackmore’s Night Temple Of The King (orig. Rainbow)  Street Of Dreams (Orig. Rainbow)  Streets Of London (Orig. Ralph McTell)  Highland (Orig. One More Time)  There are many others, but that’s enough for one band Eleanor Rigby - Blonde On Blonde (Orig. The Beatles)  Hey Bulldog - The Gods (Orig. The Beatles)  All Along The Watchtower - Affinity (Jimi Hendrix)  Coconut Grove - Affinity (Lovin’ Spoonful)  Hi Ho Silver Lining - Jeff Beck (Attack)  Actually this one is uncertain, The Attack recorded the track first, but Jeff Beck released first. Bohemian Rhapsody - Bad News (Queen)  My White Bicycle - Neil (Nazereth)  Hole in My Shoe - Neil (Traffic)  Eve Of Destruction - The Pretty Things (Barry McGuire)  Witchi Tai To - Topo D. Bil (Jim Pepper)  Somebody To Love - Bedpost Oracle (Not sure maybe Jefferson Airplane)  Badside Of The Moon - Toe Fat (Elton John)  Monster Mash - The Bonzo Dog Doo-Dah Band (Bobby Picket And The Cryptkickers)  All By Yourself In The Moonlight - Roger Ruskin Spear (Whispering Jack Smith)  I’m going to stop there, but there are a lot more OQ: What are some really great cover songs?
